      • checkMove

        public void checkMove(State state,
                      Action a)
               throws BoardException,
                      ActionException,
                      StopException,
                      PawnException,
                      DiagonalException,
                      ClimbingException,
                      ThroneException,
                      OccupitedException,
                      ClimbingCitadelException,
                      CitadelException
        Description copied from interface: Game
        This method checks an action in a state: if it is correct the state nothing happens, if it is wrong it throws a specific exception
        Specified by:
        checkMove in interface Game
        Parameters:
        state - the state of the game
        a - the action to be analyzed
        Throws:
        BoardException - try to move a pawn out of the board
        ActionException - the format of the action is wrong
        StopException - try to not move any pawn
        PawnException - try to move an enemy pawn
        DiagonalException - try to move a pawn diagonally
        ClimbingException - try to climb over another pawn
        ThroneException - try to move a pawn into the throne boxe
        OccupitedException - try to move a pawn into an ccupited box
        ClimbingCitadelException
        CitadelException
